# .gitignore — rendered into a ticket-work repo by /configure-workspace (from templates/gitignore.tmpl).
# Edit the kit template, not this file, if you want the change to propagate to other repos.

# ── Ticket exports are customer data → they go to the docstore (Drive/SharePoint), NOT git ──
# Anchored with **/ so it matches at ANY depth (tickets/<assignee>/<id>/final_deliverables/).
# An UN-anchored `final_deliverables/*.csv` matches only a top-level dir and silently commits every
# nested ticket export — the exact PII leak this pattern prevents. Enforces "exports → Drive, not git".
**/final_deliverables/*.csv
**/final_deliverables/*.tsv
**/final_deliverables/*.xlsx
**/final_deliverables/*.parquet
# Deliverable SQL, QC SQL, and READMEs are reviewable artifacts — keep committing those.

# Downloaded attachments are inputs you didn't author and often carry PII — keep them local.
# Uncomment to enforce (you can still `git add -f` a specific small input you mean to track):
# **/source_materials/*
# !**/source_materials/.gitkeep

# ── Per-user / per-install (never shared); the team-shared .claude/settings.json IS committed ──
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/worktrees/

# ── Python ──
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.venv/
venv/
.env

# ── OS / editor ──
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~
.idea/
*.iml
